HOUSE BILL 1050
F1, J1 6lr2910
By: Delegate Feldmark
Introduced and read first time: February 9, 2026
Assigned to: Ways and Means
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 State Department of Education – Organ Donation – Development of Educational
3 Materials
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the State Department of Education to consult with a certain
5 entity that operates the donor registry and procurement organizations in the
6 development, updating, or approving of certain educational materials relating to
7 organ, eye, and tissue donation; and generally relating to educational materials
8 relating to organ, eye, and tissue donation.
9 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
10 Article – Education
11 Section 1–101(a) and (f)
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
14 BY adding to
15 Article – Education
16 Section 7–455
17 Annotated Code of Maryland
18 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
19 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
20 Article – Estates and Trusts
21 Section 4–501(a), (h), (r), and (v)
22 Annotated Code of Maryland
23 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
24 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
25 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
26 Article – Education
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
